text.tspan: International tourist departures per 1000 people vs GDP per capita, 2017
International outbound tourists are the number of departures that people make from their country of usual residence
for any purpose other than business. The data on outbound tourists refer to the number of departures, not to the
number of people traveling. Thus a person who makes several trips from a country during a given period is counted
each time as a new departure.
Source: Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
